2026-03-25T18:06:36.984Z JOY-002A comment.added "Design decisions from planning session 2026-03-25:\n\n1. Capabilities are always written into the item YAML at creation time. No implicit resolution from type defaults at runtime. This makes items self-describing and stable across Joy version changes.\n\n2. Item templates live in data/items/*.yaml (embedded in the binary, same mechanism as other data/ files). Each template defines required and optional capabilities for that type. joy add reads the template and writes required capabilities into the new item.\n\n3. The item has a flat capabilities list -- no required/optional split. Optional capabilities only exist in the template as suggestions for joy add (e.g. joy add story --capabilities plan,design,implement,review adds design beyond the default).\n\nExample template (data/items/story.yaml):\n  type: story\n  capabilities:\n    required: [plan, implement, review]\n    optional: [design, test, document]\n\nExample created item:\n  capabilities: [plan, implement, review]" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-25T18:06:40.977Z JOY-002B comment.added "Design decisions from planning session 2026-03-25:\n\njoy show must visually separate item data (from YAML) and derived data (from other sources). Capabilities are now stored in the item YAML, so they appear in the main section. Jobs (from .joy/jobs/) appear in a footer section below a separator.\n\nLayout:\n  [Item data: type, status, priority, assignee, capabilities, description]\n  ----\n  [Footer: Jobs from .joy/jobs/, matched by item ID]\n\nNo mixing of stored and derived data in the same visual block. The footer makes clear that jobs are external references, not part of the item file." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-25T18:06:43.120Z JOY-0031 comment.added "Confirmed in planning session 2026-03-25: Jobs are separate files in .joy/jobs/, never embedded in item YAML. joy show displays them in a visually separated footer section. This keeps one source of truth per fact: item data in the item file, job data in job files." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-25T18:10:09.785Z JOY-002A comment.added "Update: optional capabilities removed from templates. Templates only contain default capabilities as a flat list. No required/optional split. Users override with joy edit --capabilities when needed. Example template data/items/story.yaml: capabilities: [plan, implement, review]" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-25T18:13:19.129Z JOY-002A comment.added "Plan: Capability enum in model/, item templates in data/items/*.yaml, capabilities field on Item struct (optional, backfilled on next edit), joy add reads templates, joy edit --capabilities for overrides. Starting implementation." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-25T18:13:19.132Z JOY-002A item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
